Download LTC

  The system can be used via the included LTC Editor or with Emacs.

  Use the {{{./downloads/ltc-install.sh}ltc-install.sh}} (right-click and "Save As...") bash script to automatically
  fetch the latest JAR file to a location of your choice and optionally extract the Emacs Lisp files to your Emacs
  directory.
  You can obtain usage information by invoking the script this way:

+----
$> sh ltc-install.sh -h
+----

  For example, if you want to use Emacs and the directory <<<~/Library/Preferences/Emacs>>> as the place where you
  store mode files for Emacs, you may want to call the script via (where <<<~/tmp/LTC>>> is the installation location):

+----
$> sh ltc-install.sh ~/tmp/LTC ~/Library/Preferences/Emacs
...
Done with installing LTC in ~/tmp/LTC
To start LTC server with default options, use the following command:

  java -jar ~/tmp/LTC/LTC.jar

+----

  Or, download {{{./downloads/LTC-${project.version}.jar}LTC-${project.version}.jar}} manually.
  To use it with Emacs, the JAR file contains the necessary Emacs Lisp files for <<<ltc-mode>>>.
  You can extract those files with the <<<jar>>> tool (as explained in the
  {{{./html_multipage/manual/manualch1.html}installation chapter of the manual}})
  or you may download the files individually here:

  * {{{./downloads/emacs/xml-rpc.el}xml-rpc.el}}

  * {{{./downloads/emacs/versions.el}versions.el}}

  * {{{./downloads/emacs/ltc-mode.el}ltc-mode.el}}

